The systematic uncertainties on the hadronic-fake background due to background subtraction in the hadronic-fake control regions A, B, and C are estimated by varying up and down the signal by 100%, the other MC-based backgrounds by 50%, and the other data-driven backgrounds by their estimated uncertainties, separately. The statistical uncertainties in the three data control regions are also considered. Systematic uncertainties arising from the correction factor θMC\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
